<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
MADNESS: About Jay Sand 
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" 
VLINK="#0000FF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4><BR>
<B>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Dr. JAY SAND III, esq.</FONT> 
<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="me.jpg"><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE><FONT SIZE=+2>
Jay Sand is a journeyman writer, musician and all-around sooper dooper guy.  Here he is, in fact, looking quite serious and respectful in his natural habitat -- on the couch in his apartment.  This picture is from last October, way back when the plant was still alive.</FONT></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<A NAME="home">
Jay Sand was born and raised in the ho hum capital of the world, Harrisburg Pennsylvania.  Say <A HREF="hpautho1.htm">hello</A> to his youth.
<P><BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><FONT SIZE=+1>
Jay attended the Harrisburg Academy in Wormleysburg, PA (right across the Harvey Taylor Bridge from downtown H-burg itself) from first grade until he graduated high school.  Jay learned three important lessons in school: </FONT></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
1) You must study hard and use your mind if you want to go far<P>
2) Try your darndest and you will succeed in whatever you set out to do, and<P>
3) Never drink whiskey before gym class, especially on dodgeball day.
</FONT>
<P>
<IMG SRC="yahtze2.jpg" ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=5>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
Jay moved gracefully from the Harrisburg Academy to the University of Pennsylvania where he studied American History, played quarterback for the school's undefeated Ivy League Champion football team and learned to lie voraciously.  This skill helped him tremendously in the writing of his Senior Honors Thesis, <I><A HREF="http://www.dorsai.org/~wbai/fass/index.html">The Radio Waves Unnameable</A></I>, a landmark study of counterculture radio station WBAI and its role in developing the social movements of the late '60s, and in occasionally covering social protest issues for Philadelphia's largest regional newsweekly, <I><A HREF="http://www.cpcn.com">City Paper</A></I>.</FONT>
<P>
Jay currently spends most of his time putting together <FONT SIZE=+2><A HREF="../index.htm" TARGET="_top">MADNESS</A></FONT>, the Web's premier work of subversive cyberfiction (he gets a great kick out of creating MADNESS every week, and though many folks enjoy it he must admit that he does it mainly for himself), playing guitar under a number of pseudonyms in clubs all around the Northeast and writing articles about non-violent direct action and social protest issues.  He is unnaturally concerned with making his mark on the world, and will keep dreaming big dreams until someone slaps some sense into him.
<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1>
Jay Sand is currently available for weddings, bar mitzvahs and ship christenings.  You may contact him at <A HREF="mailto:jay@user1.channel1.com">jay@user1.channel1.com</A> with your own rants, raves, dreams and desires.  Meanwhile, click the arrows below:
</FONT>
</CENTER>
