<H1>Recent Los Alamos Publications</H1>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <H2>IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT <BR>
  RECENT LOS ALAMOS PUBLICATIONS</H2>
  <P><BR>
  Los Alamos Publications is a listing of recent publications that have been
  received in electronic form. <B><EM>Please note</EM></B> that only a small
  percent of Los Alamos technical reports in electronic form can be found
  here. If you are trying to locate <B><EM>all</EM></B> electronic Los Alamos
  reports, consult the following resources.<BR>
  <BR>
  The Research Library's <A HREF="opac">online catalog</A> and <A HREF="http://bighorn.lanl.gov:4003/repcoll.html">Los
  Alamos Unclassified Publications Database</A> index the entire collection
  of unclassified Los Alamos technical reports in electronic form. The on-line
  catalog is available without restriction. However, access to Los Alamos
  Unclassified Publications is currently restricted to Los Alamos National
  Laboratory.<BR>
  <BR>
  Detailed <A HREF="http://lib-www.lanl.gov/libinfo/opac.htm">instructions</A>
  describe how to use the online catalog to<BR>
  access the wealth of Los Alamos technical reports from 1943 to the present<BR>
  now accessible electronically. <BR>
  <BR>
  For additional information on technical reports, see our <A HREF="http://lib-www.lanl.gov/infores/reports/reports.htm">Technical
  Report Resources</A> page.</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT><B>The following Los Alamos Publications are available
for access by all users.</B></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P>The majority of these Los Alamos publications are archived on-line as
  Adobe Acrobat PDF files. Click here to download the <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/Acrobat/readstep.html">free
  Adobe Acrobat Reader</A><BR>
  <BR>
  <HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>
  <H3><A HREF="la.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/bluecube.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> Recent
  Formal Los Alamos Reports</A></H3>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <H3>(LA-Series Reports)</H3>
    <P>Los Alamos Reports, LA-series reports are the vehicle for formally presenting
    the results of the Laboratory's research. Through this medium, our researchers
    share their work with their technical peers both inside and outside the
    Laboratory.</P>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>
  <H3><A HREF="lalp.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/bluecube.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
  Recent Los Alamos Laboratory Publications</A></H3>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <H3>(LALP-Series Reports)</H3>
    <P>Los Alamos Laboratory Publications, LALPs is a catchall category that
    includes all the formal Laboratory publications that are not LA-URs or
    LA-series technical reports. These publications, mostly nontechnical are
    exemplified by mini-reviews, public communications publications, capabilities
    brochures, and technical bulletins.</P>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>
  <H3><A HREF="laur.htm"><IMG SRC="/images/bluecube.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
  Recent Los Alamos Unclassified Releases</A></H3>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <H3>(LA-UR-Series Reports)</H3>
    <P>Los Alamos Unclassified Releases, LA-URs are journal articles, conference
    papers, abstracts, and publications that have not gone through the Laboratory's
    formal editing process. These documents are submitted in draft form or
    must conform to the particular style and format dictated by the journal
    or conference.</P>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>
