<h2>Hot Topics and News Sources</h2>


<center>
<a href="#hot">Hot Topics |
<a href="#general">General News Sources</a> | 
<a href="#headlines">Headlines</a> | 
<a href="http://lib-www.lanl.gov/infores/hot/cold.htm">Previous Hot Topics</a> |
<a href="http://www-map.lib.umn.edu/news.html">Maps In The News</a> |  
</center>
<hr>
<p>
<b><a name="hot">Hot Topics</b>
<dl>
<dt>
<a href="http://search.nytimes.com/web/docsroot/yr/mo/day/early/us-nuke-update.html">
Nuclear Arms Builders Move From Creators to Custodians</a>
<dd>Article from <i>New York Times</i>, Jan. 6, 1997.


<dt><a href="http://lib-www.lanl.gov/infores/hot/halebopp.htm"> Comet Hale-Bopp</a>
<dd>Have fun in 1997 tracking the comet across the sky.
<dt>New Secretary of Energy Named: Fredrico Pena
<dd><a href="http://www.dot.gov/ost/secretary.html">Biography of Pena</a> From the Dept. of Transportation

<dt>O'Leary Press Conference, Dec. 9, 1996
<dd><a href="http://www.doe.gov/html/doe/whatsnew/pressrel/pr96176.html">Energy Secretary Unveils Strategies to Reduce Global Nuclear Danger</a>
<dd><a href="http://www.doe.gov/html/doe/whatsnew/pressrel/rgndfact.html">Document FactSheets</a>
<p>
<dt><a href="http://lib-www.lanl.gov/la-pubs/00326133.pdf">Environmental Assessment for the Transfer of the DP Road Tract to the County of Los Alamos, Los Alamos, New Mexico, Predecisional Draft.</a> 
Issued Nov. 15, 1996. Requires Adobe Acrobat to read.
</dl>







<b><a name="general">General News Sources</b>
(Web versions of major news sources are not complete editions)<br>
<dl>
<dt><a href="http://www.abqjournal.com">Albuquerque Journal</a>
<dt><a href="http://www.asianweek.com/">AsianWeek</a>
<dd>The national English language newsweekly for the rapidly growing Asian Pacific American community. Includes cover stories and some selected articles.
<dt><a href="http://antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov/apod/astropix.html">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a>
<dt><a href="http://www.centraleurope.com">Central Europe Online</a>
<dt><a href="http://www.csmonitor.com">Christian Science Monitor</a>
<dt><a href="http://www.cnn.com">CNN Interactive</a>
